This document will provide stats and info on personal Spotify extended streaming data which can be downloaded from your Spotify privacy settings by selecting the Extended streaming history box and clicking Request Data.
Data recorded includes offline data as data is stored in app and uploaded once the device is connected to the internet.
In this report, listening to a song is defined as playing it for at least 10 seconds.

Summary Stats

  • Data in this report is up to 26 October 2023.
  • Listening history on your account dates back to 23 March 2017 with the first song played at 22:45 that day.
  • Over the history of the account:
    • Youve spent 277,556 minutes (4,626 hours) playing music. That equates to 115 minutes per day, or 8.0% of the time your account has been active!
    • Your most played song is Moving to New York by The Wombats, which has been played 223 times in 6.6 years, or once every 10.8 days.
    • Youve played songs from 1,714 unique artists.
    • Your favourite artist is Arctic Monkeys, which youve spent 24,095 minutes (402 hours) listening to, across 140 different songs.
    • Youve played 446 podcast episodes, from 27 different shows. Your most listened to show is JaackMaates Happy Hour, with 94 hours listened.
